<emphasis id="B97DEA859C77FF9EC3D8F98AFEB9F9B3" bold="true" box="[151,289,1584,1610]" pageId="3" pageNumber="386">Description</emphasis>
. 
<figureCitation id="13322A129C77FF9EC27FF98AFE01F9B3" box="[304,409,1584,1610]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1885,1909]" captionTargetBox="[166,1421,179,1859]" captionTargetId="figure-24@4.[166,1421,179,1859]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Light microscopy images of Geocenamus longus, female. A) Entire body; B) Pharyngeal region; C) Pharyngeal region with a visible hemizonid near to the excretory pore; D) Anterior end of the body, the structure of the cuticle; E) Anterior end of the body with a visible long stylet; F) Vulval region with a visible filled spermatheca; G–I&amp;M) Vulval region; J–K) Tail region with a visible anus; L) Tail region with a visible phasmid. Scale: A) 50 µm; B–M) 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6538169" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6538169/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="386">Figures 1</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation id="13322A129C77FF9EC280F98AFE78F9B3" box="[463,480,1584,1610]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1581,1605]" captionTargetBox="[170,1416,181,1557]" captionTargetId="figure-19@5.[170,1416,181,1557]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Light microscopy images of Geocenamus longus, male. A) Entire body; B) Anterior end of the body with visible long stylet; C) Pharyngeal region; D) Lateral field; E) Posterior region with visible testis; F–G) Tail region with visible spicules; H–I) Tail region with a visible bursa. Scale: A) 50 µm; B–I) 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6538171" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6538171/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="386">2</figureCitation>
. Measurements see 
<tableCitation id="C68B032C9C77FF9EC18FF98AFCA4F9B3" box="[704,828,1584,1610]" captionStart-0="TABLE 1" captionStart-1="TABLE 2" captionStart-2="TABLE 3" captionStartId-0="6.[148,236,599,625]" captionStartId-1="7.[151,239,151,175]" captionStartId-2="8.[148,236,644,670]" captionTargetPageId-0="6" captionTargetPageId-1="7" captionTargetPageId-2="8" captionText-0="TABLE 1. Morphometric measurements of Geocenamus longus from fixed females mounted in glycerin from three populations from Poland. All measurements except for percentage and ratios are given in µm and in the form, mean ± stdv (range)." captionText-1="TABLE 2. Morphometric measurements of Geocenamus longus from fixed males mounted in glycerin from two populations from Poland. All measurements except for percentage and ratios are given in µm and in the form, mean ± stdv (range)." captionText-2="TABLE 3. Comparison of morphometric measurements (expressed in ranges) of Geocenamus longus from previous and current study. In bold font are given the values that exceeded the ones obtained in previous studies or reported for the first time for this species. (-)—information not given by an author or not applicable." httpUri-0="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF76661F9C72FF9BC3DBFDEDFC01FD6C" httpUri-1="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF76661F9C73FF9AC3D8FF2DFE87FF0E" httpUri-2="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF76661F9C7CFF95C3DBFD3EF927FD3B" pageId="3" pageNumber="386" tableUuid-0="DF76661F9C72FF9BC3DBFDEDFC01FD6C" tableUuid-1="DF76661F9C73FF9AC3D8FF2DFE87FF0E" tableUuid-2="DF76661F9C7CFF95C3DBFD3EF927FD3B">Tables 1–3</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB636979C77FF9EC388F9EEFCFBF82F" blockId="3.[151,1436,1584,2007]" pageId="3" pageNumber="386">Female. Body straight to slightly bent ventrally when relaxed. Cuticle consists of two layers, tessellated with longitudinal striae at mid-body.Annuli 2.5–3.5 µm wide, flattened, striae shallow, irregular longitudinal striae divide the annuli into small blocks. Lateral field of adults with six lines, weakly crenated. Lateral field of juveniles with four lines only. Inner incisures sometimes not seen but lateral field crossed by short irregular transverse and oblique striae. Head offset by constriction, with 6–8 (mostly 7) annuli. Labial disc conspicuous. Cephalic framework weakly developed, not refractive. Labial annules divided into six segments by longitudinal striae. Stylet long and slender, cone longer than shaft, basal knobs relatively small, well developed. Deirids absent. Nerve ring slightly behind median bulb. Hemizonid near to excretory pore. Glandular pharyngeal basal bulb elongated, cylindrical. Vulva transverse with double epiptygma sunken into a distinct cavity, vagina swollen near vulva. Ovaries outstretched, paired. Spermatheca, round, well developed, filled with sperm cells. Phasmid situated at mid-tail. Tail tapering evenly to an irregularly striated terminus, bearing 23–35 annuli.</paragraph>
<caption id="DF76661F9C70FF99C3D8F8E7FBF3F818" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6538169" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6538169" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6538169/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="387" startId="4.[151,250,1885,1909]" targetBox="[166,1421,179,1859]" targetPageId="4">
